{
  "stem": "18575.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Another group will pick up those same rocks and bring them back or put them someone else, constantly on a run.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The food was a thin slice of bread in the morning and a soup, thin soup, in the evening with a-- there was, like-- like a beet type that you feed the cattle.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's a big beet, white beet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Forgot the name of it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This is-- was a standard fare.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the terror was horrendous, not only from the SS, but from the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On the block that I was in, on field four-- that was a men's field, field four in Majdanek-- my-- my block leader was a Warsaw Jew, a porter.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was a porter before the war. 'Porter' means carrying bags.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was a sadistic bastard, beating prisoners, big guy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know if he got their food portions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was another one like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We used to call him Moishe Gazal-- [? 'gazal' ?] means 'devil'-- or Herr Moishe de [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gazal. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I got beaten by him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But worse than that, I-- one time, the kommando-- we had to straighten out the stones, on our knees, between the wires, between the fences in the camp.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were two fences, electrified fence, and then there was a-- a very fine stone, and another fence.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had on our knees.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the commander of the camp, Kramer, Obersturmfuhrer Kramer-- 'Krah-mer'-- K-R-A-M-E-R-- was riding his horse along the-- along the wires, along the fences.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he didn't like-- or somebody fell down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he ordered punishment, beating.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had placed a-- a special bench they had for beating, for whipping, where you lay down.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They strip your pants off, exposing your buttock.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And two prisoners with whips would beat you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were 25 whips.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
